@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

# ==============================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION & ACCESS TOKEN VARIABLES
# ==============================================================================
# After completing Step 2 (Login), copy the 'access_token' value from the 
# response body and paste it right here:
@token = paste_your_jwt_here_after_logging_in


# ==============================================================================
# STAGE 1: ACCOUNT REGISTRATION & LOGIN
# ==============================================================================

### 1. Register a New Member
# ACTION: Run this first to seed a user account in your Neon database.
# EXPECTED: 201 Created. Returns the user object without the password hash.
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@ulads.edu",
  "password": "securepassword123"
}

### 2. Login (Run this to generate your JWT)
# ACTION: Run this after registering. 
# EXPECTED: 201 Created (or 200 OK depending on your route setup).
# RESPONSE: Contains the "access_token". COPY that token and paste it into 
# the '@token' variable at the very top of this file.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@ulads.edu",
  "password": "securepassword123"
}


# ==============================================================================
# STAGE 2: PROTECTED SELF-SERVICE USER ACTIONS (Requires @token)
# ==============================================================================

### 3. Complete Profile (Protected)
# ACTION: Ensure your copied JWT is pasted in the @token variable at the top.
# NOTICE: No UUID needed in the URL anymore! The backend relies entirely on the token.
# EXPECTED: 200 OK. Returns updated profile fields with 'is_profile_complete = true'.
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/complete-profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Jane Doe",
  "level": 200,
  "graduation_year": 2027
}

### 4. Partial Update (Update Level Only)
# ACTION: Run this to test updating single fields dynamically on the logged-in user.
# EXPECTED: 200 OK. Returns user object with updated level value.
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "level": 300
}


# ==============================================================================
# STAGE 3: PASSWORD RECOVERY (Nodemailer + Mailtrap Integration)
# ==============================================================================

### 5. Request Password Reset Link
# ACTION: Fire this endpoint to simulate a forgotten password scenario.
# EXPECTED: 200 OK with success confirmation message.
# VERIFICATION: Open your Mailtrap inbox. You should find a new email with a reset link.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@ulads.edu"
}

### 6. Reset Password Using Mailtrap Token
# ACTION: Extract the long token from the link inside the Mailtrap email 
# (e.g., /reset-password?token=XYZ...) and paste it over the token property below.
# EXPECTED: 200 OK. Your password_hash updates, and the token is invalidated in the DB.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "REPLACE_WITH_HEX_TOKEN_FROM_YOUR_MAILTRAP_INBOX",
  "new_password": "mybrandnewsecurepassword2026"
}


# ==============================================================================
# STAGE 4: ACCOUNT DEACTIVATION (Requires @token)
# ==============================================================================

### 7. Soft Delete / Deactivate Account (Protected)
# ACTION: Run this to ensure the user can securely trigger their own account deactivation.
# EXPECTED: 200 OK. Sets 'is_active = FALSE' in the database.
# VERIFICATION: If you try to log in again using Step 2, it should fail.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}